snippet.textDisplay: 1: Bran flakes, NOT corn flakes.   2: THOROUGHLY crush the flakes - don't pussy-foot about - they should almost be a powder.   3: DO NOT freeze the ice cream after shaping...   4: Shape the ice cream, then IMMEDIATELY coat with the bran flakes/cinnamon/sugar combination. (BTW... garbanzo beans??? WTF? Bran flakes, cinnamon, and sugar - NOTHING ELSE!)    5: Freeze for an hour AFTER coating. 6: Then you can fry them. (BTW... deep fryers work so much better, because it needs to be very hot - it needs to crisp the outside before the inside begins to melt.) 7: Top with chocolate syrup OR honey, followed by whipped cream and a cherry. 8: Enjoy.
